CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 20, 1953, page 22, reads: "Jammed Session - A scene typical of each session when hundreds of anxious homemakers lined up on Bedford Avenue waiting to gain admission to the free Home Service Fair held in Ammon Center."
TitMainTitle: Crowd of men and women gathered on sidewalk outside Ammon Center for 1953 Pittsburgh Courier Home Service Fair, horizontal version
